{
  "texts": [
    "Although Gemini with ZS was the most consistent approach, the model with CoT showed the lowest Fleiss Kappa values and percentage scores.",
    "In addition to our findings, an overview of the models' performance on existing non-nutrition-focused knowledge and reasoning benchmarks are indicated in Table 5.",
    "The performance scores of these three benchmarks were collected from the following references 38, 39, 48.",
    "The GPQA benchmark 49 includes 448 multiple-choice questions on biology, physics, and chemistry.",
    "The MMLU benchmark 50 contains multiple-choice questions from 57 topics, such as elementary mathematics, US history, computer science, and law; and the DROP benchmark 51 consists of 96,567 questions focusing on discrete reasoning over the content of paragraphs, including addition, counting, and sorting."
  ]
}